OL,5,C#162,500 for Berwick-upon-Tweed
OL,6, A painting by "matchstick figures"
OL,7, artist LS Lowry is to take up permanent
OL,8, residence in the Northumberland town
OL,9, that inspired it.
OL,11,FBerwick Museum and Art Gallery paid
OL,12,F#162,500 for Beach Scene, painted circa
OL,13,F1960, which depicts sand dunes in
OL,14,FSpittal in Berwick.
OL,16,FThe Lancashire artist, known for his
OL,17,Findustrial scenes, regularly visited
OL,18,Fthe North East for more than 40 years.
OL,20,FThe museum said it was "thrilled" with
OL,21,Fthe painting.
